Cook rice according to package instructions and set aside to cool. Combine soy sauce and sugar in a separate small bowl and set aside. Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add egg and cook, stirring until just set. Remove to a bowl and set aside. Add the ground beef and vegetables to the pan and cook until meat is browned. Season to taste with salt, pepper and ginger, cooking for 1 minute. Increase heat to high and add the rice, stirring for 1 minute. Stir in soy sauce mixture and egg. Serve immediately.